MatrixComponent.ManufacturerOrSourceName: Interchemol S.A., Poland and BASF, Germany

Mixing.Description: a calculated amount of MDI was added to the PTMG to obtain a prepolymer. (MDI:PTMG ratio, 2.6:1)
prepolymer was mixed with 1,4-BD while stirring at a NCO/ OH molar ratio of 1

ChooseParameter.Other: mixture was annealed at 100 C for 24 hours to complete reaction.

Matrix.Description: polymer matrix PU is synthesized from monomers, MDI and 1,4- Butanediol (1,4-BD)

ChooseParameter.Other: A 9:1 mixture of concentrated H2SO4/H3PO4 (360:40 mL) was added to a mixture of graphite flakes (3.0 g, 1 wt equiv) and KMnO4 (18.0 g, 6 wt equiv), producing a slight exotherm to 35-40 C

Cooling.Description: mixture was cooled to rt and poured onto ice (400 mL) with 30% H2O2 (3 mL)

ChooseParameter.Other: mixture was sifted through a metal U.S. Standard testing sieve
After centrifugation for 4 hrs at 4000 rpm, the supernatant was decanted away
remaining solid material was then washed in succession with 200 mL of water, 200 mL of 30% HCl, and 200 mL of ethanol. (this was done twice)
for each wash the mixture was sifted, filtered, and centrifuged with same conditions as previously stated.
material remaining was coagulated with 200 mL of ether
resulting suspension was filtered over a PTFE membrane with a 0.45 micrometer pore size

Drying-Evaporation.Description: solid was vacuum-dried overnight at rt.

MoldingInfo.Description: samples were casted on Teflon sheet

Dielectric_and_Impedance_Spectroscopy_An.Description: Gathered dielectric measurements in frequency range of 102 - 106 F/Hz, at 25 C

Rheometery.Description: controlled-stress rheometer, with parallel plate geometry
